                <details class="faq-item" open>
                  <summary>How does the process work from start to finish? <span class="faq-icon"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"><line x1="6" y1="1" x2="6" y2="11"/><line x1="1" y1="6" x2="11" y2="6"/></svg></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Simple and transparent. We start with a free 30-minute strategy call to understand your business and goals. Once the contract is signed we start immediately — no waiting, no delays. The build runs as a focused 3-week sprint with full visibility at every stage.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>What do you need from me to get started? <span class="faq-icon"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"><line x1="6" y1="1" x2="6" y2="11"/><line x1="1" y1="6" x2="11" y2="6"/></svg></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Just the basics — your business goals, target audience, and any branding you already have such as a logo, colors, or photos. We will contact you for any additional information we need along the way. No branding yet? We can handle that too as part of our branding service.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Will I be involved during the build? <span class="faq-icon"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round"><line x1="6" y1="1" x2="6" y2="11"/><line x1="1" y1="6" x2="11" y2="6"/></svg></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Yes, and your involvement makes the difference. We share progress at every stage of the design — header, footer, sections — as each part is completed. To keep the project moving on schedule, we ask that you review each finished stage promptly and provide your feedback before we move to the next one. This keeps us inside the 3-week timeline and avoids delays on both sides.</p>
